  <title>How to stop Solids turning red</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword>Model-Editor<keyword>How to stop Solids turning Red</keyword></keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">How to stop Solids turning red</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_">How to stop Solids turning <text style="color:#ff0000;">Red</text> as your mouse-pointer moves over them.</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">In the <text styleclass="Interface">Model-Editor</text>, <text styleclass="Interface">Solids</text> turn to the Selection-Color<text style="font-weight:bold; color:#ff0000;">&#32;</text>as you mouse-over them (default color in<text style="color:#3c3c39;">&#32;</text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Edit-ApplicationSettings" style="color:#3c3c39;">Application-Settings &gt; Graphics tab</link><text style="color:#3c3c39;">)</text>&#32;</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">To stop this, filter for an element that is <text styleclass="VariableName" style="color:#ff0000;">not</text> in the <text styleclass="Interface">Model-Editor</text>. </para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">For example, <text styleclass="T_Menu">Filter for Points</text>.<text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Element">Points</text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"> are not in the </text><text styleclass="Interface">Model-Editor</text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">, and therefore </text><text styleclass="Interface">Solids</text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"> are not selected as you move your mouse-over them. </text></para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#343400;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="SeeAlso">See <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Selection-Filters">Filters menu (Filters toolbar) &gt; Filter Points</link>.</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
  </body>
</topic>
